title: Irish election: first-ever Saturday general election vote
title_page: Irish election: first-ever Saturday general election vote - BBC News
maintext: Traditionally, islanders have voted ahead of the rest of the country to ensure that bad weather does not hamper the return of ballot boxes to the mainland in time for the count, which will start on Sunday.
